[4] Fiji
Date: Thu 25 Sep 2008
Source: Fijivillage.com [edited]
<http://www.fijivillage.com/?mod=story&id=2509084774a49b17212071ab72ff62>


Over 1000 cases of dengue fever have been reported around the country.

Director of Curative Health Services Dr Ami
Chandra said majority of the cases are reported
in the Central Division, adding the public should
assist the Health Ministry in the clean up and
spraying campaign and destroy mosquito breeding
places and the mosquito population.

Meanwhile, senior health inspector Waisale Delai
said they are yet to receive response on the
success of their campaign.

Senior doctors are currently attending a Cooperative Planning Workshop.

--
