******
[8] Guyana
Date: Mon 22 Sep 2008
Source: Caribbean Net News [edited]
<http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/news-10872--42-42--.html>


The Ministry of Health in Guyana has indicated
that there are reports that approximately 300
people are affected by dengue in that country.

The Kaieteur News newspaper stated that, having
been alerted by the outbreak of the fever in
neighbouring Trinidad and Tobago, the ministry
has intensified its surveillance and discovered
the large number of individuals affected.

It is the highest number of dengue cases in the Republic since 1998.

A statement from the Ministry of Health said that
the Health Department would ensure that an
adequate standard of treatment was given to those
affected and that steps were being taken to
prevent others from being infected.

The Mosquito Control Programme is also expected to be revamped.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur A-Lan Banks
